The president hesitated for three months, but nothing better happened to him, so at least he tricked the general over 10,000 military.
He managed to get Europe to promise another 5,000, even though he had at least 10,000 previously.
The most problematic of Obama's entire strategy seems to be his goal, to start withdrawing the troops from Afghanistan in 18 months and finalizing this procedure in three years. Obama's whole doctrine generated more questions from the answers he offered.
Many doubt that the increase bears the same fruit as the procedure in Iraq.
Despite the fratricidal wars in recent years, Iraq's society is relatively well organized, its leaders respect the agreements.
The situation in Afghanistan is different: no one can be trusted and no agreement is reached.
Under these conditions it is difficult to prepare the Afghan security forces, if they are used to changing the boss every day according to their needs.
Political institutions, although formally established, will remain only a people of Potemkin, after which patriarchal tribal relations will remain.
Balancing the interests of different ethnic groups is extraordinarily complicated due to confusing relations, even more complicated by the Pakistani and Iranian influences.
Not even establishing a state that is - capable of action - a minimum objective of the entire operation, seems very real.
Obama's strategy horizon is shocked by his voluntarism.
Over the past eight years, the situation in Afghanistan has continued to worsen and is now about to explode.
Only a romantic soul, who knows nothing about reality, can believe that the military sent to the war so that - they return home soon - will do some miracle here.
From the political point of view, setting the date of withdrawal of troops is pure irresponsibility, since the Taliban will consider it an indirect declaration of American defeat.
The last NATO summit showed that Europeans are increasingly less willing to participate in military operations in Afghanistan.
European politicians do not know, nor do they want to explain to their constituents, how much the security of Germany or Italy has to do with the war with Hindu Kush.
